vocabulary.definition: having a refined knowledge of the ways of the world; cultured
vocabulary.example: The new art gallery showcased a sophisticated collection of contemporary pieces.

vocabulary.definition: one of the soft, light things that cover a bird's body
vocabulary.example: The peacock displayed its colorful feathers during the mating ritual.

vocabulary.definition: having a nap; taking a short sleep
vocabulary.example: After a long day at work, he decided to take a quick nappy on the couch.

vocabulary.definition: to exceed or go beyond in degree or excellence
vocabulary.example: Her performance in the competition surpassed all expectations.

vocabulary.definition: the outer layer of cells covering an organism, in particular
vocabulary.example: The dermatologist examined her epidermis for any signs of irritation.

vocabulary.definition: to break the connection of or between
vocabulary.example: The power outage disconnected the entire neighborhood from the internet.
